The Five Shadow Games (Structural Patterns)

1. The Information Game

Core mechanic:
Control who knows what, and when.

In any system where information moves unevenly, actors gain advantage through:
	•	early access
	•	selective disclosure
	•	signal vs noise shaping
	•	intelligence gathering

Classic examples come from intelligence agencies like the Central Intelligence Agency or National Security Agency where advantage often comes simply from seeing the board more clearly.

System principle

Advantage ∝ (information quality × timing)

