2. The Incentive Game

Core mechanic:
People respond to incentives more reliably than they respond to instructions.

If you shape incentives correctly, behavior emerges automatically.

Markets, politics, and organizations all run on this.

Game-theory models from the RAND Corporation and economic theory from thinkers like John von Neumann formalized this insight.

System principle

Behavior follows reward structures.

