4. The Coordination Game

Core mechanic:
Many systems hinge on who can coordinate fastest and most reliably.

The internet, financial markets, military alliances, and social movements all depend on this.

Organizations like NATO exist primarily to solve coordination problems.

System principle

The side with faster coordination cycles often wins.

